### ============================================================
### AUDIT LOG MODULE — API LIFECYCLE TESTS
### File: backend/api-tests/audit-log.http
### ============================================================
### HOW TO USE:
### 1. Install REST Client extension in VS Code
### 2. Run: npm run dev
### 3. Run Block 0 to generate audit records first
### 4. Paste IDs into @variables below
### 5. Send each request top to bottom
### ============================================================
### NOTE: AuditLog has NO create/update/delete endpoints.
### Records are written automatically by other services.
### These tests only cover the two read (GET) endpoints.
### ============================================================


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 0 — GENERATE AUDIT RECORDS
### Perform real actions so the audit log has data to query
### ============================================================


### 0.1 — Get all users (copy manager + worker IDs)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 0.2 — Get all projects (copy a project ID)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects
Content-Type: application/json

###

### ✏️ PASTE IDs here after running 0.1 and 0.2
@managerId = PASTE_MANAGER_UUID_HERE
@workerId  = PASTE_WORKER_UUID_HERE
@projectId = PASTE_PROJECT_UUID_HERE

### 0.3 — Create a user (generates CREATE audit record for user)
# @name auditUser
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Audit Test User",
  "email": "audituser@build.com",
  "password": "TestPass123!",
  "role": "worker"
}

###

### ✏️ PASTE the new user ID here after running 0.3
@auditUserId = PASTE_AUDIT_USER_UUID_HERE

### 0.4 — Create a task (generates CREATE audit record for task)
# @name auditTask
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Audit Log Test Task",
  "priority": "high",
  "due_date": "2026-09-01",
  "created_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###

### ✏️ PASTE the new task ID here after running 0.4
@auditTaskId = PASTE_AUDIT_TASK_UUID_HERE

### 0.5 — Assign worker to task (generates ASSIGN audit record)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{auditTaskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "{{workerId}}",
  "assigned_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###

### 0.6 — Change task status: todo → in_progress (generates STATUS_CHANGE record)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{auditTaskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress"
}

###

### 0.7 — Change task status: in_progress → in_review (generates STATUS_CHANGE record)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{auditTaskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_review"
}

###

### 0.8 — Change task status: in_review → done (generates STATUS_CHANGE record)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{auditTaskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "done"
}

###

### 0.9 — Delete the audit test user (generates DELETE audit record)
DELETE http://localhost:3001/api/v1/users/{{auditUserId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 1 — GET AUDIT LOGS BY ENTITY
### GET /api/v1/audit-logs/entity/:entityType/:entityId
### ============================================================


### 1.1 — ✅ Get audit logs for the task (expect 200, multiple records)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/task/{{auditTaskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.2 — ✅ Get audit logs for a user entity (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/user/{{auditUserId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.3 — ✅ Get audit logs for a project entity (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/project/{{projectId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.4 — ✅ Get audit logs for assignment entity type (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/assignment/{{auditTaskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.5 — ✅ Get audit logs for milestone entity type (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/milestone/{{auditTaskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.6 — ✅ Pagination — page 1 limit 2 (expect 200, meta block with pagination info)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/task/{{auditTaskId}}?page=1&limit=2
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.7 — ✅ Pagination — page 2 limit 2 (expect 200, next page of records)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/task/{{auditTaskId}}?page=2&limit=2
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.8 — ✅ Default pagination (no params — expect 200, defaults to page 1 limit 20)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/task/{{auditTaskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.9 — ✅ Query for entity with no audit records (expect 200, empty array)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/task/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.10 — ❌ NEGATIVE: invalid entityType not in allowed list (expect 400)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/invoice/{{auditTaskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.11 — ❌ NEGATIVE: entityType is a number (expect 400)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/123/{{auditTaskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.12 — ❌ NEGATIVE: entityId is not a UUID (expect 400)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/task/not-a-uuid
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.13 — ❌ NEGATIVE: page=0 below minimum (expect 400)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/task/{{auditTaskId}}?page=0
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.14 — ❌ NEGATIVE: page=-1 negative (expect 400)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/task/{{auditTaskId}}?page=-1
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.15 — ❌ NEGATIVE: limit=0 (expect 400)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/task/{{auditTaskId}}?limit=0
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.16 — ❌ NEGATIVE: limit=200 exceeds maximum of 100 (expect 400)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/task/{{auditTaskId}}?limit=200
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.17 — ❌ NEGATIVE: limit=101 just over the maximum (expect 400)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/task/{{auditTaskId}}?limit=101
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 1.18 — ❌ NEGATIVE: page is a string word not a number (expect 400)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/task/{{auditTaskId}}?page=first
Content-Type: application/json

###


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 2 — GET AUDIT LOGS BY USER
### GET /api/v1/audit-logs/user/:userId
### ============================================================


### 2.1 — ✅ Get audit logs for manager user (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/user/{{managerId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.2 — ✅ Get audit logs for worker user (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/user/{{workerId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.3 — ✅ Get audit logs for deleted user (expect 200, records still exist)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/user/{{auditUserId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.4 — ✅ Pagination — page 1, limit 3 (expect 200, meta block)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/user/{{managerId}}?page=1&limit=3
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.5 — ✅ Query user with no audit records (expect 200, empty array)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/user/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.6 — ❌ NEGATIVE: userId is not a UUID (expect 400)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/user/not-a-uuid
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.7 — ❌ NEGATIVE: userId is empty string (expect 400 or 404)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/user/ 
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.8 — ❌ NEGATIVE: page=0 for user query (expect 400)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/user/{{managerId}}?page=0
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.9 — ❌ NEGATIVE: limit=500 for user query (expect 400)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/user/{{managerId}}?limit=500
Content-Type: application/json

###


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 3 — VERIFY AUDIT RECORD CONTENT
### Check the actual data inside the audit records
### ============================================================


### 3.1 — ✅ Get task audit log — verify STATUS_CHANGE records exist
### Expected: records with action: "STATUS_CHANGE", old_values, new_values
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/task/{{auditTaskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###
### After running 3.1, verify each record contains:
### ✏️ Check: action field is one of CREATE, UPDATE, DELETE, STATUS_CHANGE, ASSIGN, UNASSIGN
### ✏️ Check: entity_type = "task"
### ✏️ Check: entity_id = your auditTaskId
### ✏️ Check: STATUS_CHANGE records have old_values: { status: "..." } and new_values: { status: "..." }
### ✏️ Check: records are ordered by created_at DESC (newest first)

### 3.2 — ✅ Get user audit log — verify CREATE and DELETE records exist
### Expected: CREATE record when user was created, DELETE when soft-deleted
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/user/{{auditUserId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###
### After running 3.2, verify:
### ✏️ Check: a CREATE record with new_values containing name, email, role
### ✏️ Check: a DELETE record with old_values containing name
### ✏️ Check: no password_hash in any values (security check)

### 3.3 — ✅ Verify meta block structure in paginated response
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/audit-logs/entity/task/{{auditTaskId}}?page=1&limit=2
Content-Type: application/json

###
### After running 3.3, verify the response contains:
### ✏️ Check: meta.page = 1
### ✏️ Check: meta.limit = 2
### ✏️ Check: meta.total = total number of records
### ✏️ Check: meta.totalPages is calculated correctly
### ✏️ Check: meta.hasNext is true if more pages exist
### ✏️ Check: meta.hasPrev is false on page 1


